          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>24 May 1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Phila</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I wrote you a short<lb/> time since introducing
                                                  <persName>Dr Haas</persName><lb/> to your
                                        attention in the letter I<lb/> informed you that our
                                        Corelig=<lb/>ionist <persName>Cap Rothschild</persName>
                                        had<lb/> received the Knighthood of<lb/> Da<add>?</add> our
                                        King for the<lb/> ability he had shown as charge<lb/> from
                                        the Dominican government<lb/> to the Danish court for the
                                        pur=<lb/>pose of making a treaty with<lb/> the parties—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have since (on the <date>12</date>)</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>of <date>July</date> been appointed by the<lb/> government of these
                                                  <placeName>Islands</placeName>
                                        <del>pl</del><lb/> Stadshaupment<add>?</add>; &amp; on the
                                                  <date>12</date><lb/> of the present month
                                        elected<lb/> by my fellow citizens a member<lb/> of our
                                        Burgher or town council</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The most pleasing part of<lb/> the latter honor is
                                        that my<lb/> colleagues 5 in number have<lb/> in respect to
                                        my conscientious<lb/> convictions attend or changed the<lb/>
                                        day of meeting from <date>Saturday</date><lb/> which was the
                                        day of meeting<lb/> always to <date>Thursday</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Now I will ask the favor<lb/> of you to give this
                                        a place<lb/> in the Occident not letting it</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">appear that it came from<lb/> me. Also to pay a
                                        handsome<lb/> compliment to my colleagues<lb/> of the
                                        Burgher Council for the<lb/> liberality of feeling &amp;
                                        respect<lb/> of conscientious convictions, put<lb/> the
                                        article in your usual good<lb/>
                                        <sic>stile</sic> &amp; <del>remb</del> remember that<lb/>
                                        this is the second time I have<lb/> been fortunate enough to
                                        have<lb/> public days appointed to be<lb/> held on our
                                                  <date>Sabbath</date> changed<lb/> to days of the
                                        week.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am Dr Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
